    "We also found that stories checked by Snopes were more frequently mentioned ( 33.18 replies on average) than stories checked by PolitiFact ( 27.52 replies on average).",
    "This was also confirmed by a Mann-Whitney U test ( U = 5493496, p = 5.11 • 10 -4, twotailed).",
    "We also observed that significant ini- tial fact-checking efforts on Twitter coincided with the 2016 US presidential election, as shown in Fig. 3b.",
    "This figure also indicates that fact-checking remained prevalent in the following years, with a peak in 2020, possibly due to the emergence of COVID-19 and the 2020 US presidential election.",
